Text: The King is giving a Festival
I wish to go to the Festival-
I wish my cow would give us some milk
I wish we had a child
I wish to go to the Festival
I wish you'd give us some milk
I wish we might have a child
You wish to go to the Festival?
The poor girl's mother had died-
You wish to go to the Festival?
What, you wish to go to the Festival?!
-and her father had taken for his new wife-
-a woman with two daughters of her own.
I still wish to go to the Festival
You still wish to go the Festival-
She still wants to go the Festival-
All three were beautiful of face, but vile and black of heart
Jack, on the other hand, had no father, and his mother-
Well, she was not quite beautiful-
I wish my son were not a fool
I wish my house was not a mess
I wish the cow was full of milk
I wish the walls were full of gold-
I wish a lot of things...
Ugh, you foolish child! What in Heaven's name are you doing with the cow inside the house?
A warm environment might be just what Milky-White needs to produce his milk
It's a she! How many times must I tell you? Only "she"s can give milk
It's for my Granny in the woods
To bring my poor old hungry
Just a loaf of bread, please...
Cinderella's stepmother had a surprise for her.
I have emptied a pot of lentils into the ashes for you. If you have picked them out again in two hours' time, you shall go to the Ball with us.
... and a few of those pies...
Listen well, son. Milky-White must be taken to market.
But, Mother, no-he's the best cow-
Was. Was! She's been dry for a week. We've no food nor money, and no choice but to sell her while she can still command a price
But Milky-White is my best friend in the whole world!
There are bugs on her dugs
There are flies in her eyes
There's a lump on her rump
Big enough to be a hump-
We've no time to sit and dither
While her withers wither with her-
And no one keeps a cow for a friend!
I sort of hate to ask it
But do you have a basket?
And save some of those sweets for Granny!
Hurry up and do my hair, Cinderella!
Here, I found a little tear, Cinderella!
Can't you hide it with a hat?
What's the good of being good
Nice good nice kind good nice-

Because the Baker had lost his mother and father in a baking accident-well, at least that's what he believed-he was eager to have a family of his own, and was concerned that all efforts until now had failed
We have sold our last loaf of bread...
It's the Witch from next door...
Of course you have no bread!
It's not what I wish. It's what you wish
Nothing cooking in there now, is there?
The old enchantress went on to tell the couple that she had placed a spell on their house.

In the past, when you were no more then a babe, your father brought his young wife and you to this cottage. They were a handsome couple, but not handsome neighbors. You see, your mother was with child and she had developed an unusual appetite. She took one look at my beautiful garden and told your father that what she wanted, more than anything in the world was...
Greens, greens, and nothing but greens:
Cause I caught him in the autumn
I should have laid a spell on him
Could have turned him into a stone
Or a dog or a chair
But I let him have the rampion-
You can let me have the baby
No. But you had a sister.
But the witch refused to tell him any more of his sister. Not even that her name was Rapunzel. She went on:

I thought I had been more than reasonable, and that we all might live happily ever after. Well how was I to know what your father had also hidden in his pocket? You see, when I had inherited that garden, my mother had warned me I would be punished if I were ever to lose any of the...
I admit it was a pleasure-
And I laid a little spell on them-
But I'm telling you the same
Now listen to me, Jack. Lead Milky-White to market and fetch the best price you can. Take no less than five pounds. Are you listening to me?
Now how much are you to ask?
This is not a time for dreaming
And you can't just sit here dreaming pretty dreams
Into the woods to journey's end-
Into the woods to sell a friend-
Oh, someday you'll have a real pet, Jack
Meanwhile, the witch, for purposes of her own, explained how the Baker might lift the spell:
Go to the wood and bring me back
One: the cow as white as milk
Two: the cape as red as blood
Three: the hair as yellow as corn
Four: the slipper as pure as gold
Now may I go to the Festival?
You'd make us the fools of the Festival
Look what I found in Father's hunting jacket.
The witch's beans! We'll take them with us.
I know you are fearful of the Woods at night
The spell is on my house
Only I can lift the spell
The spell is on my house
No, no, the spell is on our house
We must lift the spell together
The spell is on our house
No. You are not to come and that is final. Now, what am I to return with?
The cow as white as milk
The cape as red as blood
The hair as yellow as corn
The slipper as pure as gold-
The cow as white as milk
The cape as red as blood
The hair as yellow as corn
The slipper as pure as gold...
And so the baker, reluctantly, set off to meet the enchantress' demands. As for Cinderella:
I still wish to go to the
Festival The cow as white as milk
But how am I ever to get to The cape as red as blood
The Festival? The hair as yellow as corn-
I'll visit Mother's grave The slipper...
The grave at the hazel tree The slipper as pure as gold...
And tell her I just want to go The cow, the cape
To the King's Festival... The slipper as pure as gold-
I have to take the journey
Into the woods, the path is straight
Into the woods to lift the spell-
Into the woods to visit Mother-
Into the woods to fetch the things-
Ting why I'm (you're) on the journey
Into the woods to get the money-
Into the woods to lift the spell-
Into the woods to Grandmother's house...
Into the woods to Grandmother's house...
No need to be afraid there-
There's something in the glade there...
Cinderella had planted a branch at the grave of her mother and she visited there so often, and wept so much, that her tears watered it until it had become a handsome tree
I've been good and I've been kind, Mother
Doing only what I learned from you
Why, then, am I left behind, Mother
Is there something more that I should do?
What is wrong with me, Mother?
What, child? Specify. Opportunity is not a lengthy visitor and good fortune, like bad, can befall when least expected
Do you know what you wish?
Are you certain what you wish
If you know what you want
And you shall have your wish
Silver and gold throw down on me
I'm off to get my wish...
The sun won't set for hours
Just one would be so boring
Then something fresh on the palate
When you're talking to your meal!
I guess this is goodbye, old pal
I hate to see us part, old pal
I hope that when I do
It won't be on a plate
Take the cow and go home!
I was trying to be helpful
Magic beans! We've no reason to believe they're magic. Are we going to dispel this curse through deceit?
No one would have given him more for that creature.We did him a favor. Least now they'll have some food
Do we want a child or not?
Or you live to regret it
And it's just a little bent
What's important, really, is the size
That I hadn't thought to explore
And he made me feel excited-
How could I know what was in store?
Where lie secrets that I never want to know
At the end of the path
So we wait in the dark
And we're brought into the light
And we're back at the start
In a cape and a hood
And take extra care with strangers-
Isn't it nice to know a lot?
Now the Prince, what was he like?
Is he charming? They say that he's charming
And it made a nice change
He has charm for a Prince, I guess...
I don't meet a wide range...
Are you to return to the Festival tomorrow eve?
Perhaps? Oh, to be pursued by a Prince. All that pursues me is tomorrow's bread
What I wouldn't give to be in your shoes
An enormous vine growing next to that little cottage!
It looks like a giant beanstalk rising into the sky
Sometimes the things you most wish for are not to be touched...
The harder to get, the better to have...
Never wear mauve at a ball...
The difference between a cow and a bean
Is a bean can begin an adventure...
Slotted spoons don't hold much soup...
The prettier the flower, the farther from the path...
The closer to the family, the closer to the wine...
The mouth of a wolf's not the end of the world...
A servant is not just a dog, to a Prince...
Opportunity is not a lengthy visitor...
You may know what you need
But to get what you want
Better see that you keep what you have
(The following lines overlap, or are spoken simultaneously)
Sometimes the things you most wish for are not to be touched...
The harder to get, the better to have...
One midnight gone... One midnight gone...
Never wear mauve at a ball...
Slotted spoons don't hold much soup...
To get what you want better keep what you have...
One midnight gone... One midnight gone...
Into the woods, then out of the woods
There are giants in the sky!
There are big, tall, terrible giants in the sky!
You just how small you are
A big, tall, terrible giant at the door
A big, tall, terrible lady giant sweeping the floor
And you know things now that you never knew before
And it's then that you long
You steal what you can, and run!
The roof, the house, and your mother at the door
The roof, the house, and the world you'd never thought to explore
And you think of all of the things you've seen
And you wish that you could live in between
There are giants in the sky!
There are big, tall, terrible, awesome, scary, wonderful giants in the sky!
Why does she run from me?
The heart she has won from me?
When the one thing you want
Is the only thing out of your reach
When you know she would go with you
You are everything maidens could wish for!
And you see her up there
And she's just out of reach
That can cut like a knife!
I must have her to wife
You're getting us through the woods
You're not the man who started
It takes patience and fear and despair
Who can tell if you do?
But what needs to be done
I'm meeting you in the woods
I know we'll get past the woods
Beyond witches and slippers and hoods
Safe at home with our beautiful prize
Wanting a ball is not wanting a Prince...
Near may be better than far
Near may be better than far
You can never love somebody else's child-
The greatest prize can often lie
At the end of the thorniest path...
Two midnights gone. And the exhausted Baker and his wife buried the dead Milky-White
What were you not to do?
What have I been to you?
What would you have me be?
It was lonely atop that tower
I am no longer a child. I wish to see the world
Don't you know what's out there in the world?
Someone has to shield you from the world
Princes wait there in the world, it's true
Princes, yes, but wolves and humans, too
Who out there could love you more than I?
What out there that I cannot supply?
The world is dark and wild
Stay a child while you can be a child

Text: On the steps of the Palace-
And it came to pass, all that seemed wrong was now right, the kingdoms were filled with joy, and those who deserved to were certain to live a long and happy life
And it's not just for today
All the curses have been ended
And the paths would often swerve
But they never lost their nerve
And they (we) reached the right conclusions
And we (they) got what we (they) deserve!
Not a sigh and not a sorrow
Then we went into the woods
And a daughter like a flower
Then I went into the woods
Lost my power, and my flower
Had we used our common sense
You must see your wish come true
Don't be careful, don't be clever
When you see your wish, pursue
But the only thing to do-
Though it's deep, though it's dark
And though you may lose the path
You have to take the journey
Into the woods to lift the spell
Into the woods to lose the longing
Into the woods to have the child
I wish to sponsor a Festival
The time has come for a Festival...
I miss my kingdom up in the sky
I wish we had more room...
But despite some minor inconveniences, they were all content...
I never thought I'd wed a Prince...
I never thought I'd find perfection...
I never thought I could be so happy!
I didn't think we'd be this rich...
I never thought we'd have a baby...
I never thought I could be so happy!
We're so happy you're so happy!
Just as long as you stay happy
I'm going to be a perfect wife!
I'm going to be a perfect son!
I'm going to be a perfect mother!
I'm going to be a perfect father!
I'm going to see that he (she)
I never thought I'd love my life!
I would have settled for another!
Then to be set for life...
If only this cottage were a little larger
I will expand our quarters in due time
Why would we expand when we can simply move to another cottage?
We will not move. This was my father's house, now it will be my son's
You would raise your child alongside a Witch?
Why does he always cry when I hold him?
Babies cry. He's fine. You needn't hold him as if he were so fragile
I can't take care of him all of the time!
I'll care for him when he's older
We had to go through thick and thin
We had to lose a lot to win
I ventured out and saw within
I'd be so much I hadn't been!
Yes, he's fine. Are you all right?
You! Have you done this to our house?
Always thinking of yourself! Look at my garden
I was thrown to the ground. I saw nothing
What could do such a thing?
No earthquake! My garden has been trampled. Those are footprints!
Who could do such a thing?
Anything that leaves a footprint that large is no "who."
Do you think it was a bear?
Besides, you ever see a bear with forty-foot feet?
More than possible. Their fears would prove to be well-founded
Into the woods you go again
Into the woods, away from here-
Into the woods, to find a giant-!
Into the woods to Grandmother's house...
Into the woods to see what's wrong...
Into the woods to slay the giant!
To see what the trouble is...
When the one thing you want
Is a thing that you've not even seen
She has skin white as snow-
If it were not for the thicket-
Not to know what you miss
While they lie there for years-
And you cry on their biers-
That can cut like a knife!
Ah well, back to my wife...
This is the world I meant
Now you know what's out there in the world
No one can prepare you for the world
How could I, who loved you as you were
How could I have shielded you from her?
Anything can happen in the woods
Any moment, we could be crushed
Wait, wait, one moment, please! We can't do this! You have a Princess
Of course, you're right. How foolish
Foolishness can happen in the woods
Seize the moment, skies may fall
Right and wrong don't matter in the woods
Let us meet the moment unblushed
You must know that, as a peasant-
Best to take a moment present
As a present, for the moment
The Giant. I had almost forgotten
Will we find each other in the Woods again?
This was just a moment in the woods
Leave the moment, just be glad
For the moment that we had
Now I must go off to slay a Giant. But that is what the next moment holds for me
I shall not forget you. How brave you are to be alone in the Woods. And how alive you've made me feel
Did a prince really kiss me?
And did I kiss him back?
What is it about the woods?
Back to life, back to sense
Back to child, back to husband
No one lives in the woods
There are vows, there are ties
There are needs, there are standards
There's the answer, if you're clever
Face the facts, find the boy
Join the group, stop the giant
Just get out of the woods
Was that him? Yes, it was
Was that me? No, it wasn't
Just a trick of the woods
Must it all be either less or more
For those moments in the woods
Oh, if life were made of moments
Even now and then a bad one-!
But if life were only moments
Then you'd never know you had one
First a witch, then a child
Then a prince, then a moment-
Who could live in the woods?
And to get what you wish
Don't forget it for a moment, though
And it's time to leave the woods!
It's because of you there's a Giant in our midst, and my wife is dead!
You persuaded me to trade away
To get up to the giants
She made us get a cow
Is how did the second giant get down here
Cause I gave it to my wife!
So the one who knows what happened
And it isn't mine at all!
But I got it for my mother!
Yes, and what about the harp
She went and dared me to!
She said that I was scared
If you hadn't dared him to-
And you had left the harp alone
Well, if you hadn't thrown away the bean
Well, if she hadn't raised them in the first place-!
Yes, if you hadn't raised them in the first place-!
Right! It's you who raised them in the first place-!
You raised the beans in the first place!
We can always give her the boy
No, of course, what really matters is the blame
Fine, if that's the thing you enjoy
Like his son will be, too-
You'll just do what you do
Soon you'll see the sky fall!
Beans were made for making you rich!
Oh well, you can blame another witch
I'm leaving you my last curse:
You can tend the garden, it's yours
Punish me the way you did then!
Give me claws and a hunch
Comes the day you say, "What for?"
No more curses you can't undo
Left by fathers you never knew
Free from the ties that bind
Where did you have in mind?
Where are we ever to go?
For what you have left undone
And, more, what you've left behind
Can't we just pursue our lives
With our children and our wives?
All the wolves, all the lies
All the wondering what even worse is
Hard to see the light now
Things will come out right now
The slotted spoon can catch the potato...
Every knot was once straight rope...
The harder to wake, the better to have...
The greater the good, the harder the blow...
When going to hide, know how to get there
The knife that is sharp today may be dull by tomorrow...
Now we can all return home and let us hope there will be no more killing
Where am I to go? I have no one to take care of me
You'll have to take care of yourself now, Jack. It's time
No, it's not. I'll take care of him
Yes. I'll be your mother now
I don't want another mother, I want a friend. And a pet
Well, of course, we have nowhere to go, so we'll move in with you
My house is in shambles and there is hardly room for-
Of course you can come home with us
And you shall join us, too
You'll not return to the castle?
I'll gladly help you with your house. There are times I actually enjoy cleaning
How proud your wife would have been of you
And how sad it is that my son will never know her
Maybe I just wasn't meant to have children-
Of course you were meant to have children...
But how can I go about being a father
With no one to mother my child?
Do not let it grieve you
Hold him to the light now
Things will be all right now
Shhh. Once upon a time... in a far-off kingdom... there lived a young maiden... a sad young lad... a childless baker... with his wife...
Though it's deep, though it's dark
And though you may lose the path
Into the woods, but mind the past
Into the woods, but mind the future
Into the woods, but not to stray
Will help when you return there
I think I see a glimmer-
Into the woods, but not too slow-
Into the woods, it's nearing midnight-
Into the woods to mind the wolf
